metadata.name: Interdimensional Highways II #55
metadata.description:
Since the discovery of the first Interdimensional Highway, we have been getting better at charting them and improving our understanding of how they function. But we must hurry, because as we continue to prepare our vehicles, our bodies and minds for this one of a kind travel, there's still one question that remains to be answered:

Which will be our fate: to conquer... or to be conquered?

Interdimensional Highways is a two-parts series of generative artwork, showing some of the possible formations of connecting ways between multiple dimensions.

* * *

9 reserved pieces will be sent as gift to collectors who minted 4 or more pieces of Interdimensional Highways I.

Press S to save as PNG.

Made by: yenren / twitter.com/yenrenART
Made with: JavaScript + HTML Canvas
License: LICENSE.txt

metadata.name: ASTRONOMICAL #49
metadata.description:
Define your own galaxy.
How will you choose to orient the numerous, or sparse, planets?
What palette might be the topic of discussion on the James Webb Space Telescope's next discovery? 
Mould your central planet into the next ASTRONOMICAL phenomenon.

Every aspect of every aspect is randomized: the location, opacity and size of stars. The colours, division, and size of the central planet. The number and location of curves, as well as the size, colour and number of planets along each one. The thickness of the border, and the strength of the effects.

100% chance of 1 ring, 10% chance of two rings and 1% chance of three rings around the central planet.

Made with p5.js.

metadata.name: Kinetic Bug #142
metadata.description:
Best viewed on a decent GPU,  because physics simulations are performance intensive. Otherwise you might encounter a bug...

In a world of digital data, a new life is born. We are not alone...
Explore how kinetic bugs make their way through the world. What will their destiny be?
It's curious that we can sympathize to a predefined creature living it's predestined life in the digital world. Coding in the computer abyss reveals interesting worlds.

Keyboard
[ space ] - jump
[ click ] - increase velocity briefly
[ r ] - restart simulation
[ s ] - save image
[ f ] - full screen

Mobile
[ two finger tap ] - jump
[ tap ] - increase velocity briefly

Created with Three.js + rapier.js

metadata.name: Sharding #31
metadata.description:
A virtual gallery displays sculptural forms that slowly get fractured into shards by falling coins.

Summer, 2022 I had 2 (physical) art exhibitions in Santa Fe, New Mexico. Both exhibitions combined physical and digital work, including NFT's. During the exhibition period, I was struck by the spatial and temporal limitations of the physical galleries, not to mention the elitist economic model. This experience was in stark contrast to the very positive, even joyful, experience I've been having publishing NFT's, especially on fxHash.

'Sharding' explores the creation and destruction of generative knot, and related, geometries. The facetted geometry is creating utilizing the following steps:
1. curve creation
2. form extrusion
3. Verlet node creation
4. facetted face creation

The different steps enable the forms to be disassembled/reassembled into their face primitives, including accurate (enough) collision response.

Interactivity:

Mouse/Trackpad:
drag -> camera rotation
Mouse Rt Btn -> camera pan
scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
r: reassemble geometry
w: toggle wireframe on/off
-: reduce active coins
+: increase active coins
p: screen capture

Note:
Please post your favorite 'Sharding' screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node

Thank you Paul Bourke, for some of the knot equations

metadata.name: CrossWorlds #46
metadata.description:
In 2057 an error occurred in the particle accelerator machine causing a diversion in space-time that leads to duplication of our world. Scientists discovered that they can travel to these "CrossWorlds" with wormholes plagued by singularities occurring at weakened points of the fabric between worlds. In time, some worlds became hostile to each other, tried to plunder their natural resources, and take over civilizations but other worlds learned how to co-exist peacefully...
------------------
Animation_
Press R: Rotates the world 180°
Idle: Default animation cycles from corner to corner
Mouse: Cursor-dependent animation
MobileDevice: Controls the animation with the orientation of the device. (Android only)
------------------
Live-view_
Resolution: Add "&res=" end of your url with a resolution multiplier. (0.5-6)
Press S: Saves the current scene (Default 1600x1600 px).
Press L: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as PNG.
Press D: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as SVG.
------------------
Created with p5js.

metadata.name: FluxMongers #56
metadata.description:
FluxMongers are very old beings from another dimension and their spin produces huge amounts of energy and this energy discharge is what causes the realities of MAGNETIK to be distorted or even to be torn apart. Their ethereal nature, speed and might make their movements almost to be perceived as some kind of choreography but this can only be called a dance of destruction. What you are looking at is a frame frozen in their deadly dance…

FluxMongers were inspired by light paintings where the painter uses one or few sources of light to draw in the air very quickly and the drawing is captured by long exposure.

After going live,

- press ‘1’ to get a hi-res version and ‘2’ to get a medium-res version (hopefully it will work :/)

- press 's' to save a png

metadata.name: TENDER Pass #508
metadata.description:
Tender is a curatorial platform and community that helps bring incredible works of generative art to discerning collectors.

Holding a TENDER Pass enables enriched benefits and experiences within the Tender ecosystem. Passholders expand their access to unique collaborations with extraordinary artists, indispensable collector tools, curatorial experiences, artwork insights, fine art prints, a thriving community, and more.

Tender is committed to stewarding the growth of generative art and amplifying the voices of artists and collectors across the entire lifecycle: from creation to collection to curation, and back again. Every Pass minted and resold directly enables Tender to continue creating the platform and experiences that serve this mission.
